ag zur Schärfung der Rede von »Bewegungs-Kultur«.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aSociology (General). 4aCultural Studies. 4aEthnographie. 4aKörper. 4aSemantik. 4aSoziologie. 4aSport. 4aSportwissenschaft. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aBody.  aCultural Studies.  aSociology.  aSport.1 aAlbert, Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAuffarth, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFikus, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFikus, Monika, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoritz, Eckehard F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchürmann, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchürmann, Volker, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStreck, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb0 cprintz978389942261040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839402610?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839402610zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839402610/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA